The United Labour Congress of Nigeria (ULC), has bemoaned the demolition of houses by the Lagos State Government during the COVID-19 lockdown.
 
The labour centre described the action as callous, wicked, and most horrendous.
 
ULC argued that governments should not preside over the destruction of the nation by carrying out actions that put Nigeria at risk.   To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .